description:
Make the iOS background execution model explicit. T0 runs under a short UIApplication.beginBackgroundTask to finish during app-to-background transition. T1+ are scheduled via BGProcessingTaskRequest with requiresExternalPower=true.

WHY: iOS suspends backgrounded apps by default. If a download completes and the user immediately backgrounds the app, T0 work must complete or be checkpointed. beginBackgroundTask gives approximately 30 seconds of runtime on iOS 13+. BGProcessingTask gives longer runtime but is opportunistic.

PLATFORM CORRECTION -- beginBackgroundTask TIMING: On iOS 13+ (and certainly iOS 26), beginBackgroundTask grants approximately 30 seconds, NOT the old 180s. Treat the expiration handler as the EXPECTED path for T0 in background, not an edge case. The checkpoint-and-resume design must be rock-solid.

PLATFORM CORRECTION -- beginBackgroundTask THREAD SAFETY: beginBackgroundTask(withName:expirationHandler:) is safe to call from any thread as of iOS 4.0+. No @MainActor dispatch needed.

PREREQUISITE: Add .backgroundExpired to AnalysisOutcome.StopReason (defined in bd-wbg). The runner returns this when its background task expires. Add it alongside the other StopReason cases:
  case backgroundExpired  // background task time limit reached, partial progress checkpointed

